# zeroMatrix

- _zeroMatrix(m, n)_

Answers the `zero` matrix of the specified shape (_m×n_).

A 2×2 matrix:

```
>>> 2.zeroMatrix(2)
[
	0 0;
	0 0
]
```

A 2×3 matrix:

```
>>> 2.zeroMatrix(3)
[
	0 0 0;
	0 0 0
]
```

A 3×2 matrix:

```
>>> 3.zeroMatrix(2)
[
	0 0;
	0 0;
	0 0
]
```

